1 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
2 Sec. 1. 16 V.S.A. § 2857 is amended to read:
3 § 2857. VERMONT NATIONAL GUARD TUITION BENEFIT PROGRAM
4 (a) Program creation. The Vermont National Guard Tuition Benefit
5 Program (Program) is created, under which a member of the Vermont National
6 Guard (member) who meets the eligibility requirements in subsection (c) of
7 this section is entitled to the following tuition benefit for up to full-time
8 attendance:
9 (1) For courses at any Vermont State College institution or the
10 University of Vermont and State Agricultural College (UVM), the benefit shall
11 be the in-state residence tuition rate for the relevant institution.
12 (2) For courses at any eligible Vermont private postsecondary
13 institution, the benefit shall be the in-state tuition rate charged by UVM.
14 (3) For courses at an eligible training institution offering nondegree,
15 certificate training, or continuing education programs, the benefit shall be the
16 lower of the institution’s standard tuition or the in-state tuition rate charged by
17 UVM.
18 (4) For courses at a non-Vermont approved postsecondary education
19 institution approved for federal Title IV funding where the degree program is
20 not available in Vermont, the benefit shall be the in-state tuition rate charged
21 by UVM.
