1 (c) Eligibility.
2 (1) To be eligible for the Program, an individual, whether a resident or
3 nonresident, shall satisfy all of the following requirements:
4 (A) be an active member of the Vermont National Guard;
5 (B) have successfully completed basic training;
6 (C) be enrolled at UVM, a Vermont State College, or any other
7 college or university located in Vermont in a program that leads to an
8 undergraduate certificate or, a baccalaureate degree, or a graduate degree, or at
9 an eligible training institution in a program that leads to a certificate or other
10 credential recognized by VSAC;
11 (D) have not previously earned an undergraduate bachelor’s degree
12 that was funded under the Program or any other State funding source
13 designated exclusively for members of the Vermont National Guard;
14 (E) continually demonstrate satisfactory academic progress as
15 determined by criteria established by the Vermont National Guard and VSAC,
16 in consultation with the educational institution at which the individual is
17 enrolled under the Program;
18 (F) have used available post-September 11, 2001 tuition benefits and
19 other federally funded military tuition assistance; provided, however, that this
20 subdivision shall not apply to:
