1 (d) Service commitment.
2 (1) For each full academic year of attendance under the Program, a
3 member shall be required to serve two years in the Vermont National Guard in
4 order to receive the full tuition benefit under the Program.
5 (2) If a member’s service with the Vermont National Guard terminates
6 before the member fulfills this two-year service commitment, other than for
7 good cause as determined by the Vermont National Guard, the individual shall
8 reimburse VSAC a pro rata portion of the tuition paid under the Program
9 pursuant to the terms of an interest-free reimbursement promissory note signed
10 by the individual at the time of entering the Program.
11 (3) For members participating in the Program on a less than full-time
12 basis, the member’s service commitment shall be at the rate of one month of
13 Vermont National Guard service commitment for each credit hour, not to
14 exceed 12 months of service commitment for a single semester.
15 (e) Termination of tuition benefit.
16 (1) The Office of the Vermont Adjutant and Inspector General may
17 terminate the tuition benefit provided an individual under the Program if:
